*Description*

We currently use 2 endpoints to save add-ons in 2 separate scenarios:

* If the selection is making any changes to add-on subscriptions (subscribing, unsubscribing etc.) we call the subscribable-addons BFF: 
{{gw/subscribable-addons/selection}}
* If the selection doesn’t include any add-on subscriptions we use the standard meal selection endpoint: 
{{/gw/v1/carts/{WEEK}}}

We previously needed the subscribable-addons API to handle CRM emails but BE changes were made to support both cases using the standard cart meal selection endpoint, +*so we would like to stop calling the subscribable-addons API and always use the cart endpoint*+.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria* *_(focus on the what, not the how)_*

* For a user that has 3 regular meals selected:
** User can subscribe/unsubscribe from add-ons
*** User’s regular meals remain unchanged
** Users that are subscribed to add-ons are unsubscribed from all add-on on deactivation
*** User’s regular meals remain unchanged
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*Developer Information* 

* This API call needs to be updated in 2 places:
** [On the edit add-ons screen (TPT specific code)|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/blob/master/app/spaces/whitelabel/modules/whitelabel-web/packages/components/my-deliveries-components/src/elements/meal-swap-actions/hooks/useHandleSaveAddOnsTPT.ts#L91]
